SUMMARY:GameCon at House on the Hill (board game night in NW PDX/Beaverton)
DESCRIPTION:Portland Area Board Games and RPGs\nCome join us to experience a vast array of games\, ranging from party games to middleweight and heavyweight games! With 400 games at your disposal and our recurring gamers bringing dozens more\, there's no shortage of options to choose from. Our home has a dozen tables throughout the house for folks to play.\n\nOur community is very welcoming and a great place to make friends for new and experienced gamers alike. We can help you find a group to play with when you arrive or let you explore! With the event running from 4 PM to midnight\, there's practically no limit to how long the games can run. It's a great place to break out your lengthy\, heavier weight games\, but also wonderful for playing lots of shorter party games and everything in between.\n\n**BEFORE THE EVENT**\nJoin our active [Discord](https://discord.gg/RGGjPm7qqy)\, where regulars and new attendees chat about [the next event](https://discord.gg/Qp9nNPzzjT)\, [side events](https://discord.gg/Tf8nN3z32x)\, and a plethora of other fun topics. You can [schedule games](discord.gg/J3wvFM7aAW) or arrange [carpools](https://discord.gg/PmVxJQ6XdC). On Discord\, please make your username your name or nickname so other members know who you are. It really helps find people at the event!\n\nYou may want to bring:\n\n* board games\n* snacks to share\n* cat/dog allergy meds (we have 2 long-haired cats. The flooring is mostly non-carpet)\n\n**NAVIGATING GAME NIGHT**\nPlease make a name tag when you arrive\, and feel free to grab food & drinks. Folks tend to socialize for the first 30 minutes\, and new games start every 20-30 minutes.\n\nIf you have any questions during the event (including needing help finding a game to play/join)\, you can ask in the [general chat]() on Discord\, or ask one of our hosts (Kevin) or a regular attendee (many of our attendees will be able to help!)\n\n**FOOD INFO**\nWe provide snacks\, drinks\, and hot food. We encourage you to bring your favorite foods to share as well. If you bring enough for 10-15 people\, that's awesome!\n\n**GAMES INFO**\nJoin [scheduled games](discord.gg/J3wvFM7aAW) on Discord\, bring games (especially ones you can teach)\, or feel free just to show up and choose a game to play\; there are over 400 games here to choose from. You can also see games other attendees bring\, chat about your favorites\, and more on Discord!\n\nList of all board games that we have at the house: [https://geekgroup.app/users/gameconathoh/collection](https://geekgroup.app/users/gameconathoh/collection?status.wishlist=1&sort=-rating.bgg)\n[https://geekgroup.app/users/gameconathoh/lists](https://geekgroup.app/users/gameconathoh/lists)\n[https://boardgamegeek.com/collection/user/gameconathoh](https://boardgamegeek.com/collection/user/gameconathoh)\n\nPeople also bring a plethora of other games to play.\n\n**OTHER EVENTS**\n[Calendar view for PDX Games group](http://bit.ly/pdxGAMEScal)\n[Events shared by other members](discord.gg/Tf8nN3z32x)\n\n**QUESTIONS?**\n\n1. [Discord](https://discord.com/channels/972854640016232498/9740270343659463808)\n2. Comment on the Event Post\n3. Message Kevin on Meetup or at Discord: Kevin Master of Ceremony
