SUMMARY:Board Games @ SE CORE Food Carts! 
DESCRIPTION:Portland Area Board Games and RPGs\nEvery Tuesday join us as we dive into the world of gaming at CORE Food Carts. No need to worry about rain\, too much sun or a strong breeze because we’ll be set up in their large indoor space equipped with copious number of tables perfect for gaming and safe from the weather.\n\n…………………………\n\n🎉View a list of what games people are briging\, ask questions and stay connected [**via Discord**](https://discord.gg/EjUSrsPKyt)👈\n\nDuring this event enjoy GameCon’s wide selection & variety of games! Ranging from party games\, to co-ops\, to strategic middleweight and fun social deception games.\n\n**How Many People Attend?**\nWe regularly have 20 to 30 people attend with most of them arriving around 5:30 PM/6 PM.\n\n🧐Have your own games you’d like to play?\n🎉Bring them!\n\n🤔Never played board games before?\n😃No problem! We'll happily teach you in this low-pressure\, welcoming environment.\n\n😨Feeling a little nervous?\n👌That’s totally natural.\n\nNew games started about every 15 min or so\, so it doesn’t matter what time you arrive we’ll have something for you to do. Also we are happy to teach you a new game.\n\nThe thing that’s fantastic about attending board game events is it takes out the stress of not knowing what to talk about. Simply talk about the games\, ask how to play the games\, learn\, laugh\, strategize and enjoy in this welcoming environment surrounded by delicious food.\n\nIf you’re **new to town** or simply would like to expand your friend group this can be a great\, low stress way to meet new friends!\n\nIf you’re **new to games**\, this is a judgement free zone and board gamers are happy to take the time to explain and teach and\, in all truth\, love to share their hobby with new people. Because\, board games are the best games.\n\nHeavy weight games & gamers welcome as well! While its not required\, and people have brought & stared heavy weight games on the fly\, because of the time commitment for a game like this you may want join our [**Discord**](https://discord.gg/EjUSrsPKyt) to gain interest for your game and get a time set up for others to play.\n\nNewbies and veteran board gamers are always welcome!\n\n🍔**WHAT IS CORE?**\n\nCollective Oregon Eateries\, also known as CORE\, is a indoor/outdoor community gathering and food cart space that is located along 82nd Avenue.\n\nSee photos of the space below 👇\n\nThe indoor space is quite large\, 6\,500 square feet to be exact with ample amount of large tables perfect for gaming! Also provides clean bathrooms and will soon have indoor bar!\n\nOutdoors is a variety of delicious food carts to enjoy! We highly recommend sampling the bounty. See photos attached to this event to see how amazing this venue is.\n\n[**Check out CORE’s instagram**](https://instagram.com/corepdx?igshid=YmMyMTA2M2Y=) . Stay up to date with their other events.\n\nCORE has a large\, safe and free parking lot!\n\n♟️**WHAT IS GAMECON?**\n\nGameCon is the largest game night in greater Portland Metropolitan Area and we have joined forces with CORE Food Cart to bring weekly game nights to this vibrant food cart business.\n\nWant to stay connected to all GameCon’s events she thriving game boarding community?\n\nJoin us on:\n\n[**New Discord: Tuesday @CORE Events**](https://discord.gg/EjUSrsPKyt)\n\nOR\n\n[**Original Discord: Saturday @ House On The Hill Events**](https://discord.gg/kyQ6tfQk)\n\nWe have an amazing inclusive community where we just many gatherings. We are looking forward to meeting you!!!
